<section class="Section">
	<div class="Container Container--centered Container--large">
		<h1 class="u-push-3"><small>Radio4000 is a music</small> tool <small>and<br></small> a service</h1>
		<div class="Grid">
			<figure class="Grid-cell">
				<a target="_blank" href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:%27Around_the_Moon%27_by_Bayard_and_Neuville_21.jpg">
					<img src="/assets/images/illustrations/around-the-moon-bayard-neuville.jpg" alt="" />
				</a>
			</figure>
			<figure class="Grid-cell">
				<a target="_blank" href="http://pip.tamil.fr/bib/31188" class="Muted">
					<img src="/assets/images/illustrations/une-caverne-pendant-la-nuit-a-l-epoque-du-grand-ours-et-du-mammouth-emile-bayard.jpg" alt="" />
				</a>
			</figure>
			<article class="Grid-cell Grid-cell--double">
				<h2>
					<small>A service </small>for and by humans.
				</h2>
				<p>
					The musical content on Radio4000 is generated by humans who want to discover and share their music selection. You can give yourself some peace in music digging and listen to the sounds of fellow humans around you. Discover wonderful songs in the context of someone you like the taste of.
				</p>
			</article>
			<article class="Grid-cell Grid-cell--double">
				<h2>
					<small>A tool to</small> understand <small>your music discoveries.</small>
				</h2>
				<p>
					We want to provide you with some context for your music history. For example what genre it is, which label it was released on and when it came out.
					That way you'll have a better chance to dig into fresh discoveries.
				</p>
			</article>
			<article class="Grid-cell Grid-cell--double">
				<h2>
					<small>A tool to</small> manage <small>your online music.</small>
				</h2>
				<p>
					All the links pointing to the music you like, floating around the vast internet, are now stored in one place.
				</p>
			</article>
			<figure class="Grid-cell Grid-cell--double">
				<a target="_blank" class="Muted" href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Georg_Abraham_Hackert_-_Ruins_of_the_Augustan_Bridge_at_Narni_-_WGA11015.jpg">
					<img src="/assets/images/illustrations/ruins-of-the-augustus-bridge-at-narni-view-1-georg-abraham-hackert.jpg" alt="" />
				</a>
			</figure>
			<article class="Grid-cell Grid-cell--double">
				<h2>
					<small>A service </small>to extend discoveries.
				</h2>
				<p>
					The nature of each person having a single radio — and not multiple playlists — encourage exploration and will surprise you with unknown songs from all over the world.
				</p>
			</article>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<section class="Section">
	<div class="Container Container--centered Container--large">
		<h1 class="u-push-3"><small>What Radio4000</small> stands for</h1>
		<div class="Grid">
			<article class="Grid-cell">
				<h2><small>Cultural</small> diversities</h2>
				<p>
					Diferences of taste and personalities are at the core of Radio4000. We value and respect plurality of self expressions.
				</p>
			</article>
			<article class="Grid-cell">
				<h2><small>Fair </small>ecosystem</h2>
				<p>
					A platform such as Radio4000 can only exist because of the people behind, sharing their music.<br>
					Let's work on a fair and viable ecosystem leading to more music and more sharing.<br>
				</p>
			</article>
			<article class="Grid-cell">
				<h2>Privacy <small>and</small> ownership</h2>
				<p>
					Anyone can access your radio channel and listen to your selection — anytime and anywhere. No one needs to know who you are. It is about the music. The data we save about you is what's in your radio channel. If you choose to leave, we help you export your tracks, what is yours is yours.
				</p>
			</article>
			<article class="Grid-cell">
				<h2><small>Embrace the</small> future</h2>
				<p>
					We're all here to imagine and create a music experience for year 4000
				</p>
			</article>
			<figure class="Grid-cell">
				<a target="_blank" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:More_otho_flying.JPG" class="Muted">
					<img src="/assets/images/illustrations/more-otho-flying-richard-neuhauss.jpg" alt="" />
				</a>
			</figure>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

